A line of severe thunderstorms are forecast to move into southeastern Minnesota this evening.

Some storms may be capable of producing a tornado. A Tornado Watch is in effect for portions of Illinois, Iowa, Minnesota, Missouri and Wisconsin until 11 p.m. Wednesday. 

Wind gusts up to 90 mph and isolated hail are expected.

Prepare to move into a secure interior room on the lowest floor of a building should tornado warnings be issued.
